DESCRIPTION

FLSDK is a collection of Bash scripts designed to assist
users in compiling the various FLDIGI applications used by
Amateur Radio Operators.


INSTALL INSTRUCTIONS

Download:
* Download flsdk-<version>.tar.gz

Extract:
* tar -xf flsdk-<version>.tar.gz
* cd ./flsdk-<version>

Configure, make, make install:
* ./autogen.sh --prefix=/usr/local
* make
* sudo make isntall

Options:
* To disable manpage generation add --disable-manpages
* To disable documentation add --disable-docs

Example:
./autogen.sh --prefix=/usr/local --disable-manpages --disable-docs


RUN FLSDK
* Open A Terminal, then type: flsdk

SUPPORT

If you have problems with the FLSDK, please email <ki7mt01@gmail.com>

